The thermal conductivities were calculated based on the equation κ = dλCp, where the thermal diffusivities λ were measured by the TC−1200RH instrument under vacuum, with an uncertainty of <10%, whereas the heat capacities (Cp) were estimated based on Dulong–Petit rule above RT. The three physical parameters (α, σ, κ) were finalized by taking the average values of several samples tested by the same method. The total uncertainty for ZT value was ∼18%. In addition, the heat capacities (Cp) for the Se-incorporated sample Cu4Sn7.5S16−xSex (x = 1.0) were measured with the measurement system (PPMS, Quantum Design) in the temperature range of 2.0–153 K, and the Debye temperature (ΘD) was then determined using the equation19:1ΘD=(12π2nR5β)13\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
